mindmap
  root((Scalable AI Infrastructure))
    Layered Architecture
      Modular Pipelines
        - Batch, Streaming, Real-Time
        - Version-Controlled and Observable
        - Failure-Graceful Design
      Feature Stores and Registries
        - Organizational Memory
        - Discoverable Components
        - Reproducibility and Governance
      Operational Layer
        - CI/CD and Rollback Systems
        - Monitoring and Alerting
        - Baseline Production Requirements
    Platform Mindset
      From Projects to Platforms
        - Abstract Recurring Patterns
        - Shared Services and Playbooks
        - Remove Repetition Not Creativity
      Modularity and Reuse
        - Components as Products
        - Standardized Interfaces
        - Discoverability and Documentation
      Delivery Acceleration
        - Reduced Time to First Model
        - Increased Component Reuse
        - Contracted Bespoke Surface Area
    Observability and Resilience
      Real-Time Visibility
        - Data Flows and Pipeline Status
        - Confidence Scores and Anomalies
        - Structured Alerting Rituals
      Provenance and Lineage
        - Data Origin Tracking
        - Model Version Traceability
        - Audit-Ready Operations
      Self-Healing Systems
        - Automated Retry and Fallback
        - Context-Aware Escalation
        - Reduced Burnout and Downtime
    Scaling Teams
      Central Platform Team
        - Internal Products Mindset
        - Paved Roads Not Bottlenecks
        - Core Infrastructure Ownership
      Embedded Liaisons
        - Bidirectional Feedback Loops
        - Local Use Case Integration
        - Platform Extension Support
      Abstraction Layers
        - Standardized APIs and Runtimes
        - Reduced Cognitive Load
        - Guardrails With Autonomy
    Governance as Multiplier
      Access Control
        - RBAC and ABAC Policies
        - Enforceable Not Informal
        - Complexity Without Chaos
      Audit and Accountability
        - Who Did What When and Why
        - Root Cause Analysis
        - Reproducibility and Trust
      Policy as Code
        - Governance in CI/CD Pipelines
        - Schema Validations
        - Secure Paths as Default Paths
    Infrastructure Readiness
      Assessment Dimensions
        - Observability and Confidence
        - Reusability as Leverage Signal
        - Compliance and Lineage
      Portability and Extensibility
        - Cross-Environment Mobility
        - Vendor Independence
        - Integration Agility
      Automation Maturity
        - Manual Step Reduction
        - Focus People on Value
        - Spectrum Not Binary